    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup for May 4th is headlined by **Gunnar Henderson**, whose 70.02 score reflects an elite matchup against Schlittler. His favorable platoon advantage and leadoff position make him our highest-projected source of runs and stolen bases. Close behind, **Josh Lowe** (65.99) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (65.92) provide excellent stability. **Josh Lowe** benefits significantly from a high-upside matchup against Martin, where his dynamic platoon profile drives his score well above the baseline. **Heliot Ramos** (62.37) rounds out our top-tier plays; his matchup against the soft-tossing V\u00e1squez, R (xERA 4.91) presents a prime opportunity to drive in runs from the cleanup spot, despite the park penalty.\n\nThe most challenging decision today involved the marginal range, specifically balancing **Jackson Merrill** (51.80) and **Sam Antonacci** (51.68). **Sam Antonacci** secured his spot due to the leadoff advantage and a favorable xwOBA of .400, while **Jackson Merrill** edges out the bench options due to his high-volume involvement in the batting order. Ultimately, **Andy Pages** (50.24) is the final outfield start; while his raw projections were lower, we are betting on his specific situational utility against Okert\u2014his 88% stolen base potential against the opposing pitcher\u2019s slow delivery keeps him in the lineup over bench options like **Jorge Polanco** or **Nasim Nunez** to address our need for speed. \n\nWe must remain cautious with **Drake Baldwin** (44.72) and **Miguel Vargas** (47.58), both of whom are facing the formidable L. Gilbert and Soriano, respectively. While they avoid the \"below floor\" threshold, their proximity to elite arms requires close monitoring of in-game adjustments. Furthermore, while **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Jordan Westburg** remain stashed on the IL, their absence continues to compress our bench flexibility, forcing us to lean on the current active roster to carry our categories. We are currently holding **Marcell Ozuna**, **Josh Jung**, **Coby Mayo**, **Brady House**, and **Dominic Smith** in reserve; they remain on standby should any late-inning weather concerns arise, though current reports indicate all venues are clear for play.",
